    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a mechanically sorted 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) featuring the 3.6L M96 horizontally opposed six-cylinder engine. This powerplant utilizes VarioCam Plus for optimized valve lift and timing, delivering a linear power band through a 6-speed manual transaxle. This example features essential preventative maintenance including a documented IMS bearing retrofit, a recently replaced Air Oil Separator (AOS), and a low-temperature thermostat. The chassis maintains its structural rigidity and handling precision, equipped with four-piston Brembo monobloc calipers and staggered 18-inch alloy wheels. While the exterior and interior show honest signs of use consistent with its driver-tier status, the drivetrain remains free of RMS leaks or bore scoring concerns. This is a high-performance, rear-engine machine intended for an enthusiast who prioritizes mechanical integrity and analog feedback.",
